Q16_1: First signs of understandingBefore children begin to speak, they show signs of understanding language by responding to familiar words and phrases. Below are some common examples. Does your child do any of these? - Respond when name is called (e.g. by turning and looking at source)
Q16_2: First signs of understandingBefore children begin to speak, they show signs of understanding language by responding to familiar words and phrases. Below are some common examples. Does your child do any of these? - Respond to "no no" (by stopping what s/he is doing, at least for a moment)
Q16_3: First signs of understandingBefore children begin to speak, they show signs of understanding language by responding to familiar words and phrases. Below are some common examples. Does your child do any of these? - React to "There's mommy/daddy" by looking around for them.
